The paper deals with information theory and communication, specifically the problem of computation broadcast. It discusses the rate of a computation broadcast scheme and its capacity, which are concepts related to information theory. Therefore, cs.IT is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves linear algebra and optimization, which are topics related to data structures (cs.DS) and computational complexity (cs.CC). The paper also explores the significance of extra-entropic structure, which is a topic related to social and information networks (cs.SI) and networked systems (cs.NI).
